2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with the utilization of dormant base stations in UDNs, which is a networking problem. 
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper discusses the cooperation between multiple base stations in UDNs, which can be viewed as a multi-agent system. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper analyzes the performance of cooperative transmission schemes in UDNs, which can be viewed as a control problem. 
5. cs.COM (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper involves numerical simulations to evaluate the performance of cooperative transmission schemes in UDNs, which can be viewed as a computational problem.
